    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Well, this isn&#39;t gonna be too detailed as it&#39;s the same basic strategy as the old Lone Frodo deck. <br>
<br>
Try to bid 3 or 4, it&#39;s cool to go first, but with this deck it&#39;s unnecessary, as long as you play your sites. Be sure to play all that you can on Site 1 and move to your Site 2.<br>
<br>
For an indepth look at the sites and how to use them see the other deck. (The address is at the bottom.)<br>
<br>
DON&#39;T WASTE PUMP! This is imperative to the success of this deck. Try to conserve pump as much as possible, for example if you are at Site 5 and aren&#39;t going to be overwhelmed then don&#39;t waste pump to win the skirmish, take the wound, (unless you&#39;re exhausted) then move to Site 6 and heal. Again, DON&#39;T WASTE PUMP!<br>
<br>
Cycle your hand, try to double move alot, as the Shadow won&#39;t stop &#39;Uber Fellowships&#39; and save the PATHS for desparate situations. That&#39;s about it, have fun with this deck. Reviews are welcome, escpecially ones with useful tweaks.<br>
<br>
